Privacy Policy
Privacy Policy
Effective May 25, 2018
About this Policy
Random Logic Games is committed to respecting the privacy of its users and this Privacy Policy is intended to help you understand how we use your data. This privacy policy explains the types of personal data we collect, why that personal data is collected, how we collect and store your personal data and how we use the personal data that you share with us. This privacy policy also explains your data protection rights.
Random Logic Games provides gaming applications to users in multiple countries. In some cases, personal data is processed in respect to the use of a gaming application or use of Random Logic Games’ website within the EU territory. When data is processed to provide a game, product or service in the EU that personal data is subject to the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). The portions of this privacy policy that apply only to data control or processing under the GDPR are indicated with the preceding symbol and highlighted text.
Policy Updates
Occasionally we may change our privacy policy and if we do, we will update this page accordingly. This privacy policy is applicable to our website, our mobile applications, and any other product or service provided by Random Logic Games. Please visit this page from time to time to review our privacy policy.
You will be bound by the Privacy Policy when you view, access, or otherwise use the covered products and services offered by Random Logic Games. Please read this privacy policy carefully.
We recommend that you print and retain a copy for your reference.
This privacy policy was last updated on May 25th, 2018.
Who We Are
Introduction
Random Logic Games, LLC (Random Logic Games) is a mobile gaming company founded in 2013 in Birmingham, Alabama and is headquartered at 450 Century Park South, Suite 105A, Birmingham, Alabama 35226.
Our Services
Random Logic Games provides games you can play through a mobile application (the "App") or through Facebook (collectively the “Service”). You can access those games through the Random Logic Games, LLC website located at
www.randomlogicgames.com
or through an app store.
What Personal Information We Collect About You
Categories of Data We Collect
Data You Provide Us: You are not obligated to provide us with personal data beyond the limited data we need to register your account or to make payments if you purchase premium services from us. However, a complete profile helps make the Services more relevant and useful to you. We may ask you to provide the following information:
•   Name
•   Email Address
•   Telephone Number
•   Financial Information such as credit card or bank account numbers (through 3rd party payment processors described below)
•   Username/Screen Name and Password
•   Player usage data (such as how often you play a game, when you use a hint, or how many puzzles completed)
Data from Third-Parties:
We may collect data from other services, such as your Facebook ID when you play our games through Facebook.
Device and Location Data:
We will get your consent before we collect information about your precise location for a feature. We may also collect device information such as Device ID (Android) or Advertising ID (iOS devices).
Automated Technologies or Interactions:
We collect data through cookies, web beacons and other similar technologies. Please see our Cookie Policy for more detail.
We do not collect sensitive personal information.
How We Collect Your Data
We will collect and process your personal data for the purposes of providing our gaming services and products to you.
We collect personal information about you when you:
•   Download one of our applications
•   Register or set up an account with us
•   Login to our application (i.e. through Facebook)
•   Complete actions within a gaming application
•   View or click on advertisements
•   Make an in-app purchase
•   Purchase coins from the online shop
•   Sign up for service updates
•   Sign up for promotional offers
•   Send us your feedback
•   Telephone, write, email, text, contact us online, email or text us or otherwise provide us with your personal information.
How We Use Your Information
We may use your personal information to:
•   provide services and customer support as requested, including confirming emails related to the Service, reminders, and transactions;
•   provide technical support for the Service;
•   facilitate ‘emoji’ communication between interested parties registered on the Service;
•   customize your experience;
•   measure and improve the Service;
•   keep you informed about targeted marketing, service updates, and promotional offers through various means of communication (There is always an option to opt-out of marketing communications sent by email, push notifications or text message);
•   compare the information you provide with our own information for accuracy and verify it with third parties;
•   measure consumer interest in the products and services offered on the Service;
•   help promote a safe service and detect and prevent error, fraud, and other potentially prohibited or illegal activity;
•   enforce the Privacy Policy and other agreements and policies of the Service;
•   collect fees;
•   help select advertisements viewed on the Service; or
•   as otherwise described at the time of collection.
Purpose of Processing and Legal Basis
We will only collect and process your personal data when we have a lawful basis for doing so.
The legal basis that we rely on for processing your data will depend upon the circumstances in which it is being collected and used, but will in most cases fall into one of the following categories:
•   Where you have provided your consent to allow us to use your data in a certain way
•   Where we need to perform the contract we are about to enter into or have entered into with you
•   Where it is necessary for our legitimate interests (or those of a third party) and your interests and fundamental rights do not override those interests; or
•   Where we need to comply with a legal or regulatory obligation
Service providers
We use service providers to help us provide you with our Services (e.g. maintenance, analysis, audit, payments, fraud detection, marketing and development). They will have access to your information as reasonably necessary to perform these tasks on our behalf, but only to allow them to perform their services for us.
Advertising
We show you (and measure the performance of) ads when you use our Services, directly or through a variety of partners, using the following data, whether separate or combined:
•   Data from advertising technologies, such as web beacons, pixels, ad tags, cookies, and device identifiers, both on and off our Services;
•   User provided information;
•   Data from the use of our Services (i.e. player usage data such as what types of games you play, how many puzzles completed, etc.)
We will show you advertisements on our free game applications. We offer you choices regarding personalized ads, but you cannot opt-out of seeing other ads. We sell premium Services that provide users with additional gaming options, these premium gaming applications do not contain any advertisements.
Advertisement Providers
We use advertisement providers to provide advertisements to you when you use our free game applications. You will only receive personalized ads if you opt-in to doing so, but you cannot opt-out of seeing other ads. If you do not want to receive any ads, you can subscribe to our premium Services. These premium gaming Services provide users with additional gaming options and do not contain any advertisements.
We encourage you to review the privacy policies of our third-party advertisement partners:
