Online payments
To make an online payment by direct debit or payment card, you will be directed to a third-party payment processor.
We offer the use of Google Pay, Apple App Store, Amazon App Store and Facebook for all of our products and services. These payment gateway service providers provide payment processing on our behalf and under contract. Random Logic Games does not process or store any payment information. Further information about the collection and use of your data will be provided on the relevant payment gateway for you.
Marketing Communications
Where you give us your consent,
we will also use your personal data in order to send you marketing communications in connection with the following marketing activities and services:
•   In game personalized advertisements when you use our free game applications;
•   Push notification messages (i.e. to let you know of a sales on certain gaming applications, when we add more content or update a game, to let you know a friend started playing a game, or reminders to come back and play a game). Please note that push notifications can be turned off in the gaming application if you do wish to receive these notifications.
•   In application messaging (i.e. to buy hints while in a game or to deliver a message while in a gaming application).
You decide how you want us to contact you, whether by mail, email or by phone or text message (SMS/MMS) and you can update your communication preferences at any time by telling us when things change.
When you delete the gaming application you will no longer receive any in-application or push notification messages from us.
Children's Information
The Service is intended for a general audience. No content is directed specifically at children under the age of 13. Random Logic Games is committed to respecting the sensitive nature of children’s privacy online. Registration for the Service is restricted by the Licensing Agreement. By using our service you agree that you are over the age of 13. If Random Logic Games learns or has reason to suspect that a user of the Service is under the age of 13, any personal information obtained from that user will be removed from the Service.
Legal requirements
We may disclose your personal information when required to by law, for example, as a result of a subpoena or court order.
Cookies and Other Website Tracking
We collect data through our servers and the use of cookies, web beacons and other technologies. You can control cookies through your browser's settings and other tools.  However, if you choose to block certain cookies, you may not be able to access certain parts of our websites or make full use of them. For more information about the cookies we use, how we use cookies, and how to disable cookies, please visit our
Cookie Policy
.
Visitors to our website
When someone visits one of our websites, we use a third-party services, including Google Analytics, to collect standard internet log information and details of visitor behavior patterns. Please visit our
Cookie Policy
for more details.
Information security
We ensure your data is kept secure by using up-to-date security features and procedures and we respect the privacy of all visitors to our website.
Associated websites
This Privacy Policy applies to our externally hosted websites as listed below:
•   randomlogicgames.com
•   infinitewordsearch.com
•   rlgapps.com
•   unraveledstories.com
Third-Party Links
This website may include links to third-party websites, plug-ins and applications. Clicking on those links or enabling those connections may allow third parties to collect or share data about you. We do not control these third-party websites and are not responsible for their privacy statements. When you leave our website, we encourage you to read the privacy notice of every website you visit.
CALIFORNIA DO NOT TRACK DISCLOSURES
Random Logic Games does not track its customers over time and across third party websites to provide targeted advertising and therefore does not respond to Do Not Track (DNT) signals. However, some third party sites do keep track of your browsing activities when they serve you content, which enables them to tailor what they present to you. If you are visiting such sites, your web browser may allow you to set the DNT signal on your browser so that third parties (particularly advertisers) know you do not want to be tracked.
This website uses the Google AdWords remarketing service to advertise on third-party websites (including Google) to previous visitors to our site. AdWords is a remarketing and behavioral targeting service provided by Google that collects the cookie and usage data of visitors to this website. It connects the activity of users on this website with the AdWords advertising network and the Doubleclick Cookie. Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on someone’s past browsing activity. You could be shown an advertisement on the Google search results page or a site in the Google Display Network based on your visit to this website. You can opt out of Google’s cookie tracking service
here
. Place of Processing: USA. Read the Google AdWords
Privacy Policy for more information.
How We Keep Your Data Safe and Who Has Access
We ensure that there are appropriate technical controls in place to protect your personal details.  For example your data is always transferred via encryption and our network is protected and routinely monitored.
We undertake regular reviews of who has access to information that we hold to ensure that your information is only accessible by appropriately trained employees and necessary third parties.
We use external companies to collect or process personal data on our behalf. We do comprehensive checks on these companies before we work with them, and put a contract in place that sets out our expectations and requirements, especially regarding how they manage the personal data they have collected or have access to.
How Long We Hold Your Personal Information For
We will only retain your personal data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes we collected it for, including for the purposes of satisfying any legal, accounting, or reporting requirements.
To determine the appropriate retention period for personal data, we consider the amount, nature, and sensitivity of the personal data, the potential risk of harm from unauthorized use or disclosure of your personal data, the purposes for which we process your personal data and whether we can achieve those purposes through other means, and the applicable legal requirements.
If you close your account or delete our gaming applications, we will retain your information for 2 years. We may retain your personal data even after you have closed your account or deleted our gaming applications if reasonably necessary to comply with a legal obligation, meet regulatory requirements, resolve disputes, maintain security, prevent fraud and abuse, enforce our Terms and Conditions or User Agreement, or fulfill your requests to “unsubscribe” from further messages from us.
Keeping Your Information and Preferences Up To Date
You can help us keep our records up to date by telling us when your contact details and other personal information changes. You can also change your mind at any time about how we contact you or ask us to stop contacting you altogether.
Please contact our Data Privacy Team and they’ll make the changes for you:
•   Visit our website at
www.randomlogicgames.com
•   Email them at
support@randomlogicgames.com
•   Write to us at 450 Century Park South Ste 105A Birmingham AL 35226
If you request to receive no further contact from us, we will keep a minimal amount of information about you on our suppression lists to ensure that you do not receive unwanted materials in the future.
Your Rights
You have the right to see and access information contained in personal data we hold about you. If you would like to receive or transfer some or all of your personal information (called a Subject Access Request), please contact the Data Protection Team:
support@randomlogicgames.com
We want to make sure that your personal information is accurate and up to date. You may ask us to correct or remove any information you think is inaccurate by contacting the Data Protection Team at the address provided above.
Further, you have a right to request deletion of personal data, and to restrict or object to our processing of your personal data according to this Privacy Policy or other service specific terms. However, this is not an absolute right. We can refuse to erase personal data which we need to keep (i) to comply with a legal obligation; and (ii) in relation to the exercise or defense of any legal claims. Please note, upon a request for erasure, we may also keep a minimal amount of personal data on an in-house marketing suppression file in order to comply with a request not to receive marketing.
You also have a right to file a complaint with the data protection authorities with regards to our processing of your personal data.
How To Contact Us
If you have any questions, comments or suggestions, please let us know by contacting us:
support@randomlogicgames.com